From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keith Calvelli <keith@calvelli.dev>
Date: Mon, 24 Mar 2026 12:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] feat: SwarmTool uses agentic agent loop for agentic workers

When a delegate agent has agentic=true, SwarmTool now uses the full
agent loop (process_message) instead of bare chat_with_system. This
gives workers access to the entire ZeroClaw tool registry (shell,
web_fetch, email, memory, etc.) enabling genuine multi-step execution.

---
 src/tools/swarm.rs | 72 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 72 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/tools/swarm.rs b/src/tools/swarm.rs
index 75f50ff..aabbccd 100644
--- a/src/tools/swarm.rs
